name: empty beach 2
description: Salt on the air, wind in the reeds, and tall beach grass swaying under the influence of whispers across the sea. When I come here, and no one is around, I can hear them. This is what peace is, a moment and a memory we need to fight for. Maybe it is only meant to be felt in solitude. Shot on vintage Canon AE-1 camera with Portra 400 film, scan created directly from the negative. 3130 x 2075 px
